WEBVTT

00:01.345 --> 00:03.056
<i>Previously on</i> Mike & Molly...

00:03.057 --> 00:06.299
I remember when I was a little girl
working on my daddy's farm.

00:06.301 --> 00:07.735
Oh, please don't
tell me a story...

00:07.736 --> 00:08.969
Let me tell you a story.

00:08.970 --> 00:10.871
I was a meek little thing,

00:10.872 --> 00:13.874
scared of my own shadow
and the sheep I had to castrate.

00:13.875 --> 00:16.911
That's where you learned it?

00:16.912 --> 00:20.848
Just when I thought my life
couldn't possibly get any worse,

00:20.849 --> 00:24.251
a city fella in a '56 Rambler
pulled up to the house

00:24.252 --> 00:26.086
and asked for directions.

00:26.087 --> 00:28.522
- Was that Mike's dad?
- Hell no.

00:28.523 --> 00:30.758
This was a real man.

00:30.759 --> 00:33.394
Wore a three-piece suit
with hard shoes

00:33.395 --> 00:37.431
and smelled like a pine forest
after a spring rain.

00:37.432 --> 00:39.299
That's very poetic, Peggy.

00:39.300 --> 00:41.101
What he did to me wasn't poetic.

00:41.102 --> 00:42.769
It was filthy.

00:42.770 --> 00:43.670
And I loved it.

00:43.671 --> 00:46.106
All right, wait, wait,
wait.

00:46.107 --> 00:47.741
Got to write it down. Go.

00:47.742 --> 00:50.077
MIKE: <i>Look at you,</i>
writing again.

00:50.078 --> 00:52.144
Yeah, new story...
about a young girl

00:52.146 --> 00:53.814
coming of age
on a hardscrabble farm

00:53.815 --> 00:55.682
at the base of
the Mudlick mountains.

00:55.683 --> 00:56.883
Mudlick? That-that's weird.

00:56.884 --> 00:59.518
My mom grew up on a farm
in Mudlick.

01:01.988 --> 01:04.090
Oh, no!

01:08.361 --> 01:10.230
No.

01:10.231 --> 01:12.299
Really?

01:12.300 --> 01:14.266
Come on.

01:14.268 --> 01:16.937
Is there anything about
these pages that you do like?

01:16.938 --> 01:18.538
Hold on.

01:18.539 --> 01:20.739
Nope!

01:20.741 --> 01:22.943
Well, this is your life
you're crapping on.

01:22.944 --> 01:24.644
I just wrote it down.

01:24.645 --> 01:26.112
You got Mudlick all wrong.

01:26.113 --> 01:27.513
The people, the geography.

01:27.515 --> 01:30.884
How the heck did I get
from the barn dance to the car

01:30.885 --> 01:33.486
to consummate
my forbidden love with Troy

01:33.487 --> 01:35.588
when it was parked
up on McGrainey Hill?

01:35.589 --> 01:37.157
You ran! Okay...

01:37.158 --> 01:38.725
"Fueled by a burning lust

01:38.726 --> 01:40.426
that would soon consume
both of them."

01:40.427 --> 01:43.162
Now, that is a great line,
and I'm not cutting it.

01:43.164 --> 01:46.766
Why did I spend all that time
drawing you a map of Mudlick

01:46.767 --> 01:48.100
if you're not gonna use it?

01:48.102 --> 01:50.270
Really? You want to
talk about the map?

01:50.271 --> 01:51.504
Let's look at that map.

01:51.505 --> 01:52.772
Oh, here we go.

01:52.773 --> 01:57.576
"Home," "big tree," "crick."

01:57.578 --> 01:59.879
Well, if you know where
two out of three of those are,

01:59.880 --> 02:01.514
you can find your way anywhere.

02:01.515 --> 02:04.117
It's called triangulationing.

02:04.118 --> 02:06.319
This is not a map, Peggy.

02:06.320 --> 02:08.955
This is a taunt
from a serial killer.

02:08.955 --> 02:10.923
Okay, we have to go there.

02:10.924 --> 02:12.357
What are you talking about?

02:12.359 --> 02:13.860
Road trip, Peggy.

02:13.861 --> 02:15.093
We're going to Mudlick.

02:15.095 --> 02:17.229
I'm not going
back to that hellhole.

02:17.231 --> 02:21.100
Your name can go first
on the title page.

02:21.101 --> 02:22.602
Read your contract.

02:22.603 --> 02:24.971
I got that months ago.

02:24.972 --> 02:26.806
Seriously?

02:26.807 --> 02:29.407
I got to stop using Vince
as a lawyer.

